1
00:01:09,359 --> 00:01:10,159
President Huo

2
00:01:11,959 --> 00:01:12,519
President Huo

3
00:01:12,640 --> 00:01:13,680
The Old Madam is having an episode.

4
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:14,480
Quick, go check on her.

5
00:01:18,879 --> 00:01:20,359
Old Madam, please calm down.

6
00:01:20,359 --> 00:01:20,959
Old Madam!

7
00:01:20,959 --> 00:01:23,239
Grandma!

8
00:01:23,239 --> 00:01:24,799
Don't worry, I... I...

9
00:01:24,799 --> 00:01:25,760
I'm Huo Beiyan.

10
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:26,480
Look at me.

11
00:01:26,719 --> 00:01:27,680
I'm Beiyan.

12
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:31,799
Who are you?

13
00:01:32,079 --> 00:01:33,760
I won't take the medicine.

14
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:34,640
Grandma.

15
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:36,120
I'm better now. Grandma is fine.

16
00:01:36,319 --> 00:01:37,439
We don't need the medicine.

17
00:01:37,439 --> 00:01:39,120
It's okay, let me take a look.

18
00:01:46,359 --> 00:01:48,599
Patients experience hallucinations

19
00:01:48,599 --> 00:01:50,799
because vague sensory inputs

20
00:01:50,799 --> 00:01:51,640
and memory fragments

21
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,920
get incorrectly bound together.

22
00:01:53,239 --> 00:01:54,799
Due to impaired frontal lobe function,

23
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:55,799
these erroneous responses

24
00:01:55,799 --> 00:01:57,680
can't be identified or suppressed.

25
00:02:04,319 --> 00:02:06,719
There's nothing wrong with these two medications.

26
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,000
Come on, Grandma.

27
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:14,400
It's okay.

28
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,159
What are you doing?

29
00:02:15,319 --> 00:02:17,000
Extensive contact between water and skin

30
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,039
can rapidly lower body temperature.

31
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:21,639
It's raining.

32
00:02:21,879 --> 00:02:23,439
Wind and rain.

33
00:02:23,439 --> 00:02:24,120
That's right.

34
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,199
After the rain, a rainbow will appear.

35
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:27,400
Okay.

36
00:02:32,319 --> 00:02:34,000
There's no rainbow.

37
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:37,120
The cause of the hallucination is unclear,

38
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,680
but guiding its direction

39
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:40,000
can be effective.

40
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,879
Go find me a watering can.

41
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,039
A watering can?

42
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:44,199
Trust me, go quickly.

43
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,960
Grandma, it's okay.

44
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:14,719
Look, a rainbow!

45
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,479
A rainbow.

46
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:36,759
A rainbow.

47
00:04:03,439 --> 00:04:04,800
Grandma, look.

48
00:04:06,319 --> 00:04:07,560
Nange.

49
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:10,840
My good Nange.

50
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,720
Thankfully Grandma's okay.

51
00:04:34,879 --> 00:04:35,680
That's so strange.

52
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:38,120
Grandma can't remember anyone,

53
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,240
but just now,

54
00:04:39,399 --> 00:04:40,759
she only remembered your name.

55
00:04:41,079 --> 00:04:42,560
This kind of thing does happen,

56
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:43,600
but it's extremely rare.

57
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,680
I'm increasingly convinced

58
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:47,399
that my initial instinct was right.

59
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,240
Perhaps

60
00:04:49,639 --> 00:04:51,240
you really can help the Huo family.

61
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,639
Don't get your hopes up too high.

62
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,439
Alzheimer's disease

63
00:04:56,439 --> 00:04:57,600
isn't that easy to cure.

64
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,160
But I'll do my best to help.

65
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,519
President Huo.

66
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,560
President Huo.

67
00:05:08,639 --> 00:05:10,360
Senior Chairman Huo told me to bring this.

68
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:19,959
Do you know Chinese medicine?

69
00:05:20,399 --> 00:05:21,199
A little.

70
00:05:23,319 --> 00:05:24,319
Epimedium

71
00:05:24,319 --> 00:05:24,839
Rehmannia

72
00:05:24,839 --> 00:05:25,879
Deer antler slices

73
00:05:28,319 --> 00:05:28,720
Dodder seed

74
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,399
Dodder seed

75
00:05:29,399 --> 00:05:30,480
Atractylodes

76
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:31,360
Eucommia

77
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,639
What are they for?

78
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,480
Isn't it obvious?

79
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,439
Yours is an aphrodisiac.

80
00:05:35,439 --> 00:05:36,360
Mine is to prevent miscarriage.

81
00:05:39,759 --> 00:05:40,160
Um...

82
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:40,839
My dad,

83
00:05:40,839 --> 00:05:43,199
he loves researching these things.

84
00:05:44,759 --> 00:05:45,959
Health and wellness.

85
00:05:47,439 --> 00:05:48,439
Good for him.

86
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:49,600
Well...

87
00:05:50,079 --> 00:05:51,240
I still have a paper to write.

88
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,240
I'll get going now.

89
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,199
Make sure to take your tonic.

90
00:05:55,839 --> 00:05:56,680
Dr. X.

91
00:06:13,519 --> 00:06:14,839
You know him?

92
00:06:22,399 --> 00:06:23,560
Of course I do.

93
00:06:24,279 --> 00:06:26,079
I'm a medical doctor.

94
00:06:26,079 --> 00:06:28,000
I read dozens of papers every day.

95
00:06:28,079 --> 00:06:29,680
What I said just now

96
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:32,360
was a quote from Dr. X's paper.

97
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,560
Didn't I say last time

98
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,079
that we should consider Zichen's feelings?

99
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,079
Our relationship

100
00:06:46,639 --> 00:06:48,439
should last as long as possible.

101
00:06:48,439 --> 00:06:49,519
I have a proposal.

102
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,680
Go ahead.

103
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:52,959
The agreement between us,

104
00:06:52,959 --> 00:06:54,319
let's extend it to five years for now.

105
00:06:54,759 --> 00:06:55,639
Five years?

106
00:06:56,759 --> 00:06:57,600
Keep your voice down.

107
00:06:57,879 --> 00:06:58,959
My dad hasn't gone far yet.

108
00:06:59,959 --> 00:07:00,920
Huo Beiyan.

109
00:07:03,199 --> 00:07:04,000
President Huo.

110
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,920
Don't tell me you're playing for real

111
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:09,399
and have actually fallen for me.

112
00:07:14,399 --> 00:07:16,160
Whatever I, Huo Beiyan, like

113
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:16,839
or want,

114
00:07:16,839 --> 00:07:18,399
I always go straight for it.

115
00:07:18,399 --> 00:07:19,360
Why beat around the bush?

116
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,279
What kind of man would that make me?

117
00:07:20,639 --> 00:07:21,759
Aren't you a bit too full of yourself?

118
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,160
You sure?

119
00:07:27,879 --> 00:07:28,519
Fine.

120
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,480
Then I want to add a condition too.

121
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:32,879
Let's hear it.

122
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,079
I can't finish all my papers.

123
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,639
I don't need money.

124
00:07:38,759 --> 00:07:41,560
I want Hai Da Medical School's entire lab.

125
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:42,920
Done.

126
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,240
Chairman Huo, Mrs. Huo.

127
00:07:46,839 --> 00:07:48,839
The paperwork is all settled.

128
00:07:48,839 --> 00:07:51,560
This is the new nameplate for our lab.

129
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,680
Thank you, Professor.

130
00:07:55,639 --> 00:07:57,319
That was incredibly fast.

131
00:07:57,319 --> 00:07:59,000
Got it done overnight?

132
00:07:59,279 --> 00:08:01,639
That's Chairman Huo's efficiency for you.

133
00:08:01,839 --> 00:08:02,560
However,

134
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,519
by tradition,

135
00:08:03,519 --> 00:08:04,639
the unveiling ceremony

136
00:08:04,639 --> 00:08:06,959
has to be done by you personally.

137
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,639
The air on campus is so refreshing.

138
00:08:24,319 --> 00:08:26,000
From your shabby little rental,

139
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:27,480
to hauling all kinds of lab equipment

140
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,800
into our marital home,

141
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:29,839
and now taking over

142
00:08:29,839 --> 00:08:31,600
the entire medical school lab.

143
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,039
At this rate,

144
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,240
world domination is around the corner.

145
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,120
Dr. Xu.

146
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:38,639
I'll be relying on you, President Huo.

147
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:43,320
But I've always been curious,

148
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,759
what's the logic behind your business plan?

149
00:08:46,519 --> 00:08:47,720
Alzheimer's disease

150
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:48,440
is one of the toughest challenges

151
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,919
in the medical field.

152
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:52,159
Pouring in so much real money,

153
00:08:52,159 --> 00:08:53,639
aren't you afraid of losing it all?

154
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,200
This matter

155
00:08:56,519 --> 00:08:57,559
has nothing to do with profit.

156
00:08:57,759 --> 00:09:00,080
My parents were busy when I was little,

157
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,200
It was Grandma who took care of me.

158
00:09:02,639 --> 00:09:04,720
Every time I came home,

159
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:07,279
Grandma would happily wait at the door.

160
00:09:08,279 --> 00:09:09,399
But later,

161
00:09:09,679 --> 00:09:10,759
she started to forget.

162
00:09:11,879 --> 00:09:13,360
The way she looked at me

163
00:09:14,039 --> 00:09:15,639
was like looking at a stranger.

164
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,879
You probably don't understand how I feel.

165
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:22,080
Businessmen always chase profit,

166
00:09:22,639 --> 00:09:24,360
but Huo Beiyan,

167
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:26,759
no matter how cold he looks on the outside,

168
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,399
deep down,

169
00:09:28,879 --> 00:09:30,080
he's actually quite loving, isn't he?

170
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:31,440
Yes.

171
00:09:31,799 --> 00:09:33,279
I know that in this world,

172
00:09:33,279 --> 00:09:34,960
no one truly feels another's pain.

173
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,200
But I think

174
00:09:36,679 --> 00:09:37,759
if one day

175
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:39,720
someone who loved me deeply

176
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,000
suddenly stopped loving me,

177
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,639
I'd be very sad too.

178
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,440
I'd probably also

179
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:47,639
try my hardest to get that love back.

180
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:04,600
I knew it.

181
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,919
It really is Grandma's birthday.

182
00:10:14,639 --> 00:10:16,360
Temporary Marriage Agreement

183
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:18,320
Both parties, due to special reasons,

184
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,720
shall enter into a marital relationship,

185
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:20,679
valid for three months.

186
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:22,200
The wife

187
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:24,360
must cooperate to play the role of a wife.

188
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:40,879
Brother.

189
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,519
You destroyed my relationship,

190
00:10:45,399 --> 00:10:47,600
so don't blame me for taking Huo Group.

191
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:52,039
I have to win at least once.

192
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,279
What are you doing?

193
00:11:06,639 --> 00:11:07,519
I'm stewing this for Nange.

194
00:11:07,519 --> 00:11:08,159
Look here.

195
00:11:08,159 --> 00:11:09,440
The way you're handling the heat,

196
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:10,480
you've really got the knack.

197
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,320
I think it's highly necessary

198
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:13,639
for me to give you some pointers,

199
00:11:13,639 --> 00:11:14,559
and to taste-test it.

200
00:11:14,559 --> 00:11:15,759
I'm just afraid your seasoning

201
00:11:15,759 --> 00:11:16,679
isn't quite enough,

202
00:11:16,679 --> 00:11:18,240
and my daughter-in-law won't like it.

203
00:11:20,919 --> 00:11:21,919
Don't worry.

204
00:11:21,919 --> 00:11:22,919
My cooking skills

205
00:11:22,919 --> 00:11:23,759
have surpassed the master.

206
00:11:23,759 --> 00:11:24,879
They're definitely better than yours.

207
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:26,679
You sound so sure.

208
00:11:26,799 --> 00:11:27,159
Then I've got to try a bite.

209
00:11:27,159 --> 00:11:27,879
I've got to try a bite no matter what.

210
00:11:28,559 --> 00:11:29,679
I'll stew some for you next time.

211
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:34,440
When did you get so stingy?

212
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,240
Got a wife and forgot your dad, typical!

213
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,159
Nange.

214
00:11:45,559 --> 00:11:46,200
Here.

215
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,080
Get some energy in you.

216
00:11:50,399 --> 00:11:51,759
Your timing is perfect.

217
00:11:51,759 --> 00:11:52,840
I'm starving right now.

218
00:11:53,159 --> 00:11:53,720
Here.

219
00:11:57,799 --> 00:11:59,080
Fo Tiao Qiang.

220
00:12:00,639 --> 00:12:01,320
Try some.

221
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:07,919
It's delicious!

222
00:12:07,919 --> 00:12:09,159
You can even make this?

223
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:10,600
Teach me when you have time.

224
00:12:11,039 --> 00:12:12,320
How am I supposed to teach this?

225
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:15,120
I'm pretty smart, you know.

226
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:16,080
Just give me the formula,

227
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:17,240
and I can learn anything.

228
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:19,039
Cooking doesn't have formulas.

229
00:12:19,879 --> 00:12:21,000
I wonder who it was

230
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:23,120
who read research papers to cook a dish.

231
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:25,360
I'm afraid you'd blow up the kitchen.

232
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,399
That makes sense.

233
00:12:27,639 --> 00:12:29,399
Then I'll just sit back and enjoy.

234
00:12:30,879 --> 00:12:31,480
Eat up.

235
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:37,919
Huo Beiyan.

236
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:41,600
Yesterday you said you didn't like me.

237
00:12:42,279 --> 00:12:44,919
But now you come feed me every day.

238
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,000
You...

